The paper deals with evaluating the performance of generative models in image generation tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes new metrics for measuring the fidelity and diversity of generated images, which are important aspects of generative models and are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and experiments, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
